SIMPLE: poppied
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poppied
<hw>Pop"pied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See 1st
<er>Poppy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Mingled or interspersed with
poppies.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Poppied</xex> corn.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affected with poppy juice; hence, figuratively,
drugged; drowsy; listless; inactive.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>poppied</qex> sails doze on the yard.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Popping</ent>⟦br⟧
